        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Frank Zago",
          "email": "fzago@cray.com",
          "date": "2015-03-26 23:42:25.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-05-11 11:30:27.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6406 tests: fix undersized fsname and FID strings",
        "message": "LU-6406 tests: fix undersized fsname and FID strings\n\nA Lustre filesystem name is up to 8 characters, plus 1 for the NUL\nterminator. If a filesystem name is 8 characters, then the\nllapi_layout_test, llapi_hsm_test, group_lock_test and llapi_fid_test\nmay have their stack scribbled or overran when they call\nllapi_search_mounts(). Add one extra byte for the NUL character.\n\nSame issue with a FID string, which also needs an extra character for\nNUL termination.\n\nSigned-off-by: frank zago <fzago@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ic7757ebce051e12f4723e27b5b00d4db1637b384\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/14213\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
